A vector is a variable sized array Vectors are parts of Rust's support for collections fn main() { let mut v_new = Vec::with_capacity(4); v_new.push(0); v_new.push(1); v_new.push(2); v_new.push(3); let v_collect: Vec<_> = (0..4).collect(); assert_eq!(v_new, v_collect); let mut v_store = Vec::from([0; 4]); for (i, v) in v_store.iter_mut().enumerate() { *v = i; } let v_init = vec![0, 1, 2, 3]; assert_eq!(v_init, v_store);
} As part of the standard library, vectors have lots of support
